    "description": "Manufactured OpenAPI artifact for Adobe Commerce REST / GraphQL APIs. This file was synthesized by Last Mile from curated research JSON and is not vendor-certified. Use it as an agent-consumable starting point, then validate paths, schemas, authentication, and server URLs with the vendor before production use. Adobe's Commerce Web APIs documentation states that Adobe Commerce provides web services for integrating third-party software and building headless applications. The public documentation is organized into Getting Started, REST, and GraphQL sections, with REST covering available web services on the latest Adobe Commerce release and GraphQL covering query and mutation access patterns favored for frontend development. This positions Adobe Commerce as a write-capable commerce integration surface for catalog, customer, order, and frontend application workflows, but not for asset or telemetry data. Asset data is Unsupported. Telemetry data is Unsupported. Writeback is Supported.",
